Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.03,0:04:26.75,signs,,0,0,0,,{=0}{\move(1356,451,1356,564.94,17,10695)\fscx82\fscy82\frz12.08\fax0.8\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\blur0.7}Nagumo \NRyuunosuke
Dialogue: 5,0:04:17.25,0:04:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A protagonist's copy appears and lives in his place.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:23.46,0:04:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No one at home or school notices that he's a copy.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:28.06,0:04:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It perfectly copies the memories, \Npersonality, and DNA of the original.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:33.82,0:04:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If it can do all that, do you think that it's the same person as the original?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.68,0:04:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I would think it's the same person.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:44.30,0:04:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Human cells are replaced each\N day because of our metabolism.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:48.47,0:04:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our cells continuously divide and copy themselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.00,0:04:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it was done in a flash or slowly doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:55.82,0:04:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you believe a copy is the same as the original.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:59.43,0:05:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.78,0:05:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this always on yer mind?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:07.67,0:05:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the shadow sickness yesterday.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:11.18,0:05:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I also looked into the legend of Hiruko.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:14.46,0:05:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to ask you, but then Hizuru told me the details.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:20.93,0:05:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Around 300 years ago in the Edo period, \Na god named Hiruko drifted to this island.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:27.82,0:05:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Far in the past, it arrived from outside this\N realm in a place you could call outer space.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:35.96,0:05:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an organism that lived in outer space.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:39.80,0:05:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It copied nearby objects, transformed into them, and then consumed the copied data,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.79,0:05:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but it had a limited choice of objects to transform into in outer space.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:50.97,0:05:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It probably came down to Earth in the form of a meteorite.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:55.72,0:06:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It likely fell into the ocean, \Nwhere there were many things it could copy.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.39,0:06:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to this point is Hizuru's theory.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:05.88,0:06:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the rest of the story is in the \Nwritten records of the legend of Hiruko.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:10.81,0:06:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Three hundred years ago, it transformed into a whale,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:14.95,0:06:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and for some reason, it washed up on this island.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:18.30,0:06:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It copied a fisherman's daughter who came to see the whale.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:23.40,0:06:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the start of the shadow sickness.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:26.67,0:06:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,True, that's how the legend of Hiruko goes.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:29.70,0:06:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are ya saying that it's a true story?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:32.38,0:06:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:33.28,0:06:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shadows exist.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:36.38,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Like they killed Ushio and my parents,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:40.88,0:06:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll kill everyone who comes to these grounds tomorrow.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:45.72,0:06:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:47.85,0:06:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You've read too many stories.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.02,0:06:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I know yer upset about Ushio's death.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:54.21,0:06:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya need some rest.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:56.48,0:06:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I know everything.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:59.95,0:07:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Karikiri, you knew that this is a true story.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:03.74,0:07:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you've watched it all unfold first-hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:07.95,0:07:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:09.33,0:07:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:09.95,0:07:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A whale?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:18.77,0:07:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't notice at first, but Dr. Hishigata pointed you out.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:25.66,0:07:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The man on the right is Dr. Hishigata's grandfather.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:30.37,0:07:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you in a photograph that's more than 70 years old,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:34.47,0:07:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Karikiri Masahito?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:36.35,0:07:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should I say, Hishigata Shidehiko?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:39.35,0:07:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Shide!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:43.97,0:07:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Haine!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:47.91,0:07:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back here, Haine!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:49.98,0:07:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hai—
Dialogue: 5,0:08:03.13,0:08:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Haine?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:04.46,0:08:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:06.97,0:08:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:13.97,0:08:13.97,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:17.10,title,,0,0,0,,{\bord5\c&HC0A038&\blur7}Summer Time Rendering
Dialogue: 1,0:08:13.97,0:08:17.10,title,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5}Summer Time Rendering
Dialogue: 5,0:08:19.43,0:08:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei—
Dialogue: 5,0:08:26.19,0:08:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Move and I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:29.10,0:08:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What has Dr. Hishigata told ya?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:32.13,0:08:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one asking questions here!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:35.52,0:08:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the other photograph.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:41.53,0:08:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That one is from 40 years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:44.22,0:08:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hishigata's father took it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:47.63,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren't a shadow,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:49.35,0:08:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not human either.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:54.84,0:08:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Swamp Man...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:01.98,0:09:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hiruko? Why would it be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.98,0:09:04.44,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(1055,742)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Fourth loop, July 23rd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NWhile investigating the old Hishigata Clinic
Dialogue: 5,0:09:04.92,0:09:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Just a guess.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:07.54,0:09:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If it is Hiruko, Hishigata Clinic and Hito Shrine must be connected somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.45,0:09:16.87,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(576,747)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Fifth loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NFourth battery ruins, after Nagumo's and Nezu's pseudo loop
Dialogue: 5,0:09:13.88,0:09:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}The identity of the four-armed shadow could be Karikiri Masahito.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:16.87,0:09:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Bwa-huh?! The Karikiri boy?!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:19.77,0:09:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think the same thing?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:23.44,0:09:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hiruko is the mother of shadows, \Nthat makes a shrine worshiping her really suspicious.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:29.67,0:09:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Karikiri is the head priest.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:31.38,0:09:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but ain't Karikiri a human?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.60,0:09:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would the four-armed shadow hide its face?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:37.14,0:09:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If it were a shadow, it would just transform into someone else.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:41.49,0:09:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it's actually a human who's incapable of copying?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:45.51,0:09:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen it scan anything, but it did print something.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:50.76,0:09:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If the four-armed shadow is a human who \Nwears the sludge of shadows as an armor...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:58.24,0:10:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to hide its face because we'd recognize him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.71,0:10:06.71,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(78,104)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Sixth loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NAfter canceling entry to Koba Mart
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.52,0:10:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare it do that to Ryuunosuke?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.96,0:10:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The four-armed shadow must be Karikiri Masahito.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:16.93,0:10:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain after seeing our fight in your memories.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:20.18,0:10:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How could ya tell?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:22.14,0:10:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I never liked that priest.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.00,0:10:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The four-armed shadow disgusts me in the same way.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.15,0:10:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do ya mean?!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:30.29,0:10:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He can hide his face, but he can't hide what's inside.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.31,0:10:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that Nezu's shots didn't work can be explained if it's human.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:39.12,0:10:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Karikiri was at the funeral during that time.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:43.10,0:10:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he sent his shadow to the funeral.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:45.53,0:10:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If there really is a human inside, we can assassinate him.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:50.85,0:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's human, killing him is easy.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:53.91,0:10:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll casually visit the shrine, then smash him while we chat.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:58.42,0:11:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's murder!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.35,0:11:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We need more evidence.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:03.01,0:11:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We might be able to persuade him too if he's human.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:07.56,0:11:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide burned his left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:10.07,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(1301,741)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Seventh loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NAfter the battle at the gym
Dialogue: 5,0:11:10.52,0:11:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll help us find his true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.03,0:11:15.99,signs,,0,0,0,,{\an7\pos(1301,741)\fscx57\fscy57\fnIwata Mincho Old Pro H-Fate\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.5}Seventh loop, July 22nd\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NHishigata Clinic basement
Dialogue: 5,0:11:14.07,0:11:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:15.99,0:11:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide is Haine's guardian and the first child Haine bore.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:20.07,0:11:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,His original name is Hishigata Shidehiko, founder of the Hishigata Clinic.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:26.67,0:11:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is this photograph?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:30.04,0:11:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hishigata family was in charge of religious ceremonies on the island,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.61,0:11:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,until Shidehiko's father started pretending to be a doctor in the Edo period.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.22,0:11:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Did ya say Hishigata?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.94,0:11:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the Karikiris ran the shrine.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:43.93,0:11:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Karikiris and Hishigatas are related.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:47.41,0:11:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They branched off from the Hishigatas.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:52.04,0:11:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all familiar with the legend of Hiruko?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:54.86,0:12:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The day Hiruko drifted here, Hiruko became Haine, and then the islanders deified her as a god.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:01.71,0:12:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:03.23,0:12:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, Shidehiko had a child with this god.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:08.21,0:12:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The child wasn't born from a scanned shadow.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:11.84,0:12:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He got Haine's body pregnant, and she gave birth to a child.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:16.79,0:12:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He called himself a god's husband \Nand took Haine's surname, Karikiri.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:21.39,0:12:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Shidehiko also had a brother.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:24.71,0:12:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After Haine gave birth, the Hishigata family split,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:27.27,0:12:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and Karikiris became priests, \Nwhile Hishigatas were doctors.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:32.31,0:12:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So Shide is a distant relative of ours?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:36.64,0:12:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:37.53,0:12:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to the child?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:40.41,0:12:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When the child grew older,\N it was a splitting image of Shidehiko.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:45.61,0:12:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be the nature of a shadow.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:47.73,0:12:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A child from Haine's pregnancy is the father's clone.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:52.63,0:12:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when it starts.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:54.11,0:12:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shidehiko notices this and kindles a certain desire.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:58.08,0:12:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:59.55,0:13:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He made Haine copy and implant his \Npersonality and memories in the clone.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.97,0:13:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, he was reborn.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.39,0:13:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a sick bastard.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:12.02,0:13:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I hated him.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:13.86,0:13:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My father helped deliver the baby and took that photo.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,His current body was born that day.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:21.92,0:13:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shide repeated this technique.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:24.38,0:13:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He made Haine give birth to his new body over and over,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:28.11,0:13:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's how he has lived for 300 years now.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:38.85,0:13:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yer a hybrid of a human and a shadow.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:41.93,0:13:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, Shinpei. Ya don't play fair. Ya loop.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:46.54,0:13:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya can't possibly know so much in just one day.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:49.90,0:13:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a seat and have some tea. It's not poisoned.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:54.77,0:13:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So ya admit it.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:07.82,0:14:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 40 years old back then.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:12.05,0:14:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the summer of 1732, the year of the Kyoho Famine.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:18.64,0:14:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do ya know about it?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:19.93,0:14:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the textbooks.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:22.92,0:14:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a terrible harvest year.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:24.71,0:14:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Fishermen died, so we had no fish either.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.40,0:14:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, Haine showed up.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:32.13,0:14:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Islanders believed that God was in items that drifted ashore,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:37.50,0:14:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so they believed Haine was a god.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:40.43,0:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In exchange for eating the people, Haine blessed the fishing.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:44.61,0:14:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The legend is wrong there.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:48.51,0:14:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She just turned a few hundred people into shadows.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:52.02,0:14:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Shadows can easily catch fish \Nand save people from starving.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:57.75,0:15:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitogashima still exists, thanks to me.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:00.91,0:15:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:02.48,0:15:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Are ya trying to justifying what ya did?!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:05.22,0:15:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd ya kill Shinpei's parents?!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:07.90,0:15:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Same reason as you, Ushio. They got in the way.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:11.86,0:15:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They found Hiruko's grotto and tried to make it public.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:15.61,0:15:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They were a foolish couple, but Mother enjoyed her meal.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:19.60,0:15:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Unforgivable!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:21.61,0:15:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, would ya have liked it if I made 'em shadows instead?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:38.59,0:15:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm not like you.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:43.98,0:15:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna kill people, and ya don't wanna die, do ya?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.87,0:15:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why go so far to protect Haine?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:52.49,0:15:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yer human, so ya can't go home with Haine.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:57.93,0:16:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up Haine and end this.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:02.36,0:16:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not how my ending goes.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.89,0:16:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My mission is to fulfill Mother's wish.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:08.78,0:16:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dammit!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:10.17,0:16:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Goddammit!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:11.74,0:16:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And ya never know.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:13.70,0:16:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I might have a shadow.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:16.48,0:16:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something's off.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:18.71,0:16:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull the trigger!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:20.03,0:16:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't sense any shadows nearby!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:22.30,0:16:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:23.19,0:16:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why is he...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:24.97,0:16:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot, Shinpei!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:26.23,0:16:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's the only chance to kill Shide!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:29.01,0:16:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what yer thinking.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:33.04,0:16:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why ain't his left hand burned?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:37.12,0:16:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:38.98,0:16:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Shinpei. Can I move now?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:43.47,0:16:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:44.85,0:16:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take it anymore!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:46.56,0:16:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ushio!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:47.30,0:16:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait—
Dialogue: 5,0:17:27.96,0:17:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:29.81,0:17:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:32.27,0:17:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'd do it.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:34.71,0:17:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to make ya do this.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:38.46,0:17:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let ya murder someone.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:40.98,0:17:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:42.37,0:17:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my chance fer revenge.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:45.08,0:17:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yer kind, so ya woulda regretted it.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:48.17,0:17:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya view everyone as people, even me and him.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:54.17,0:17:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave all the dirty work to me.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:57.65,0:17:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ushio.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:01.95,0:18:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Lemme borrow this.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:04.86,0:18:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Did y'all hear that?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:06.32,0:18:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I killed Shide.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:25.64,0:18:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.20,0:18:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. One down.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:35.96,0:18:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shide...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:37.65,0:18:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.39,0:18:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, it can't be.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:43.73,0:18:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry, Shinpei.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:45.75,0:18:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I didn't notice...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.12,0:19:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That was so close, Shinpei.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:04.91,0:19:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess yer bird's-eye view wasn't high enough to get a complete view of the situation.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:16.56,0:19:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're going alone?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:17.74,0:19:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Persuade him?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:21.26,0:19:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm against it.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:22.47,0:19:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If Shide shows his flesh, ya gotta be able to pull the trigger without second thought.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:28.57,0:19:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll kill him.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:29.31,0:19:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wait.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:30.94,0:19:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lemme try once.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:35.36,0:19:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I don't know what's on his mind, then I can't kill him.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:42.33,0:19:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want him to tell me himself why he killed my parents.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:48.29,0:19:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Otherwise, I'll never be satisfied.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:49.98,0:19:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.54,0:19:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll endure dying once just to hear that!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.26,0:19:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm still going with.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:58.56,0:20:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If the shrine is full of shadows, \Nya won't even get close enough to talk.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.73,0:20:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ushio is right.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:06.33,0:20:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you go alone, they might try to capture you.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:13.65,0:20:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll be on the grounds too.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:16.47,0:20:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:17.63,0:20:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can we somehow hear their conversation?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:21.90,0:20:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe put a phone in yer pocket and do a group call?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:24.67,0:20:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, ya won't be able to hear the conversation clearly.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:27.92,0:20:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We just need to hear gunshots.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:33.25,0:20:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll shoot twice into his shadow to find out if he's really human.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:38.83,0:20:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you hear three shots, that's your signal to go.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:47.68,0:20:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don'tcha feel like a kid who forgot to save at the end of the game before the final boss?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:55.07,0:20:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ushio is dead.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:00.95,0:21:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Brats.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:03.70,0:21:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya thought ya could mess with my ending?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:07.58,0:21:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't worry.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:08.82,0:21:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm with ya, no matter what.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:12.04,0:21:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The only loop you'll be in is despair and regret.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:17.23,0:21:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care now.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:28.00,0:21:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei really gets led around by the nose.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:30.47,0:21:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! They're like a couple.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.60,0:21:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:37.23,0:21:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:38.91,0:21:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd Ushio go?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:41.17,0:21:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She was just there.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:47.72,0:21:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinpei?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:54.92,0:21:54.92,Default,chapter,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.90,0:22:01.56,ED,,0,0,0,,{\blur5\fad(200,200)}All traces of you vanished into the sea breeze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.56,0:22:06.56,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6173A3&\3c&H22C3F8&\blur5\fad(200,200)}But even now I still see visions of you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.64,0:22:14.34,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC3A644&\3c&HE9EBBB&\blur5\fad(200,200)}In reality I only have vivid memories
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.34,0:22:15.77,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HC3A644&\3c&HE9EBBB&\blur5\fad(200,0)}To play in my head over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.77,0:22:19.27,ED,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H9AFAF8&\blur5\fad(0,200)}To play in my head over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.57,0:22:24.67,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6989A1&\3c&H73E97B&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Even if it's all just a lie
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.67,0:22:28.79,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6989A1&\3c&H73E97B&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Please be close by my side
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.09,0:22:31.85,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6A70EE&\3c&H83EF82&\blur5\fad(200,200)}Right next to me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.25,0:22:37.60,ED,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE5D78D&\3c&HE4F4FB&\blur5\fad(200,200)}I fell for you before too long
